'''Karol Estelle Kennedy Kucher''' (February 14, 1932 in [[Shelton, Washington]] - June 25, 2004 in [[Seattle, Washington]]) was an American [[pair skater]]. With her brother, [[Peter Kennedy (figure skater)|Peter]], she won five [[United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. Championship]] titles from 1948-1952. Known as "The Kennedy Kids," they won the [[World Figure Skating Championships|World Championship]] in 1950, and the silver medal in the [[1952 Winter Olympics]].

